## Phase 2: Data Simulation & Ingestion

Since we don't have a live microservice cluster yet, we need a **synthetic data generator** that mimics Prometheus-style metrics + Jaeger-style traces with injectable faults.

### [NEW] `backend/data/simulator.py`

- Generates metrics for ~10 services: `api-gateway`, `auth-service`, `payment-service`, `order-service`, `inventory-service`, `notification-service`, `database`, `cache-service`, `user-service`, `search-service`
- Normal behavior: Gaussian noise around baselines for latency, error_rate, cpu, memory, request_rate
- Fault injection: Spike a chosen "root cause" service, then propagate degradation to downstream services with delay + attenuation (simulates real cascading failures)
- Outputs time-series DataFrame + service call graph (adjacency list)

### [NEW] `backend/app/services/ingestion.py`

- Reads simulator output (or could read from Kafka in production)
- Normalizes features into sliding-window aggregates
- Stores to DB

### [NEW] `backend/app/services/graph_builder.py`

- Builds NetworkX DiGraph from trace/call data
- Computes edge weights (call frequency, avg latency)
- Caches graph in memory for fast GNN input construction

