## Phase 3: GNN Anomaly Detection

### [NEW] `backend/app/ai_module/gnn/model.py`

- **GATAutoencoder**: Uses 2-layer GAT encoder → latent space → MLP decoder that reconstructs input features
- Training: On "normal" windows — learns to reconstruct healthy behavior
- Inference: Reconstruction error per node = anomaly score
- Attention weights provide interpretability (which neighbor influenced the score)

### [NEW] `backend/app/ai_module/gnn/graph_builder.py`

- Converts NetworkX graph + feature DataFrame → PyTorch Geometric `Data` object
- Node features: `[latency, error_rate, cpu, memory, request_rate]` (z-score normalized)
- Edge index from adjacency

### [NEW] `backend/app/ai_module/gnn/train.py` & `infer.py`

- Training loop with reconstruction loss (MSE)
- Inference returns `{service_name: anomaly_score}` dict

